    </HeadContent>

    <div class="guide-wrapper">
        <div class="guide-header">
            <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i>
            <div>
                <h1>Medical Disclaimer</h1>
                <p>Clinical responsibility and legal limits of the system</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="guide-content custom-typography">
            <section class="disclaimer-section">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-gavel"></i> Limitations of Clinical Responsibility</h2>
                
                <div class="disclaimer-card border-warning">
                    <p>
                        <strong>BiliTool.Vn</strong> was independently developed, translated, and designed based on official medical guidelines <em>(including but not limited to the AAP 2022 Clinical Practice Guideline)</em>. However, all content, interpolation charts, and calculation algorithms on this interface <strong>are absolutely not intended</strong> to replace independent clinical assessments, professional medical judgements, or direct diagnoses and intervention orders from a pediatrician or neonatologist.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Applying clinical practice guidelines using this tool always requires clinicians to carefully consider the specific clinical status of each individual infant, given the highly individualized nature of neonatal jaundice progression.
                    </p>
                    <div class="disclaimer-alert">
                        <p>
                            <i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> <strong>Clinicians, medical staff, and users of this platform voluntarily and independently assume full clinical and legal responsibility</strong> for any decisions or treatment interventions made or refused based on parameters calculated by BiliTool.Vn. The development team disclaims all liability for any damages or outcomes.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="disclaimer-section mt-extra">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> Responsibility of Parents and Families</h2>
                <p class="plain-text">
                    BiliTool.Vn is a professional clinical support platform intended for healthcare staff. If you are a parent or relative monitoring an infant, please <strong>do not make any decisions regarding phototherapy or exchange transfusion yourself</strong>. Even if the calculations indicate a low hazard level, infants must be evaluated by qualified pediatricians to screen for potential underlying causes of jaundice.
                </p>
            </section>
        </div>
    </div>
}
else if (lang == "fr")
